{"author":{"id":"673ec4ab271bd63e4f842d2f0d7b678791fd860cc22fb4cc38b8473d0a341de5"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1618232463,"nonce":"Zu8YkNomMWYL3Xb36SoF62QQSvM=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlRWRpdDo1MjE5NjA4NjM="},"target":"e987130f2c371012e239ff559f74774e8da4412442cc4a17e9673010b51fc46b","message":"We [netherlands escience center](https://www.esciencecenter.nl/) have taught the documentation lesson in a coderefinery workshop twice. This repository was of great value for that so the development effort is highly appreciated! \n\nBoth times we received the same feedback from students that although they liked learning about sphinx and readthedocs, for most of their PhD-ware projects having such an extensive documentation is overkill. Instead they want to learn stuff that is more applicable to their daily work. We decided to reshape the entire lesson to teach more about in-code documentation, what should go into a README file, and with only a short demo of sphinx + readthedocs. This turned out to be a succes and I hereby share the lesson that we taught.","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1618234119,"nonce":"VFWVDJ5ogUS9xLXHXMLTrlVU3ck=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlRWRpdDo1MjE5NzkzODM="},"target":"e987130f2c371012e239ff559f74774e8da4412442cc4a17e9673010b51fc46b","message":"We [netherlands escience center](https://www.esciencecenter.nl/) have taught the documentation lesson in a coderefinery workshop twice. This repository was of great value for that so the development effort is highly appreciated! \n\nBoth times we received the same feedback from students that although they liked learning about sphinx and readthedocs, for most of their PhD-ware projects having such an extensive documentation is overkill. Instead they want to learn stuff that is more applicable to their daily work. We decided to reshape the entire lesson to teach more about in-code documentation, what should go into a README file, and with only a